</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ R.\">R.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">489a</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">πολλάκις τεθαύμακα ὅπως . . </quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Com.Adesp.\">Com.Adesp.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.46D.</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; but more commonly, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θ. εἰ . . </foreign> I <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wonder if . . </tr_>, as a more polite way of saying I <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wonder that . . </tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:155\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.155</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg007.perseus-grc1:1140\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ OC\">OC</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1140</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg004.perseus-grc1:97a\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phd.\">Phd.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">97a</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐὰν . . λέγω, μηδὲν θαυμάσῃς</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg011.perseus-grc1:215a\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Smp.\">Smp.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">215a</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote